node_manager.name: Maia
node_manager.notes:
Node manager is a far distance north-west of the node. Node must be discovered before you can invest in the node manager.

Video Guides from MorrolanTV:

How to unlock the node
Where to find the node manager

1373.name: Kisleev Crag
1373.notes: Node is up in the mountains, you can climb up from the top of the waterfall to the south-east.

1376.name: Derko Island
1376.notes: Node manager is on top, there is a ramp up from the north-west side of the island.

1382.name: Central Cantusa
1382.notes: The node manager is to the north-west at the base of the cliff where it starts to turn into desert. To invest in the node, you have to discover it by climbing the mountain.

1383.name: Cantusa Desert
1383.notes: The node is unlocked by visiting the plateau of the mountains. The node manager is at one of the northern entrances to Muiquun (quite far away).

1384.name: Pila Ku Jail
1384.notes: The node manager is inside the larger archway entrance from the desert and has the knowledge for the node for 50 energy (currently labelled incorrectly).

1389.name: Gavinya Coastal Cliff
1389.notes: Node manager is on the beach to the east.

1393.name: Dona Rocky Mountain
1393.notes: Node is on the pla teau of the mountain. The nodemanager is also up on the mountain just slightly north of the node looking out over the desert.

1394.name: Hakoven Island
1394.notes: Island is mostly cliffs, so disembark on the beach on the north-west side of the island.

node_manager.name: Katio
node_manager.notes: Katio is in the center of the island. The two easiest ways into the island are a narrow path on the east side of the island, or an underwater tunnel on the west side.

1553.name: Pilgrim's Sanctum - Humility - Excavation
1553.requirement: 80 Energy from Tarik (Pilgrim's Sanctum - Humility Node Manager)

1566.name: Roud Sulfur Works - Excavation
1566.notes: You may need knowledge from the Sulfur Works manager a short way to the north-west of the node manager before you are able to unlock this excavation.
1566.requirement: 50 Energy from Ustouvan (Roud Sulfur Works Node Manager)

10001.name: Aakman Temple
10001.notes:
As a dungeon you cannot get this node to unlock on the map

. The node manager is on the cliff north of Pilgrim's Haven. The dungeon cannot be entered by the node manager, instead you must find a dungeon portal that spawns randomly in the desert.

10002.name: Hystria Ruins
10002.notes:
As a dungeon you cannot get this node to unlock on the map

. The node manager is down the ravine. The dungeon cannot be entered by the node manager, instead you must find a dungeon portal that spawns randomly in the desert.

settings.oceannodenotes:
This ocean node does not have a node manager. It will be automatically discovered and the fog removed by sailing near it.

To trade items fished/gathered at this node at full price you must have this node uncovered and either:
a) an unbroken path of connections must exist from the node, via discovered ocean nodes, to Port Ratt and then Port Ratt must be connected via invested nodes to the trade destination, or:
b) an unbroken path of connections must exist from the node, via discovered ocean nodes, to Lema Island and then Lema Island must be connected via invested nodes to the trade destination
